source.g: MSM stores data in one place, which users access through a dedicated portal. Relevant information stored on third-party systems is shared with MSM using data integration to support customer and employee processes. This means no more data silos or duplicate data.

In the agent console, customer and product information, built-in qualification and validation rules, and guided processes with call scripting, guide your employees through their day-to-day jobs. They have all the information they need in one place, so no need to train them on multiple systems.

Built-in qualification and validation rules, context-aware pricing structures, and validation feedback throughout the quote-and-order process give your customers and employees all the right information when they need it. This reduces employee training requirements, improves quote and order accuracy, and ultimately reduces order fallout.

The product and service catalog is modular, so you can quickly add and update products and services to incorporate new technologies. Use the prebuilt mobile and digital subscriber data structures and product models to build and customize offers fast and decrease time to market.
The customer self-service portal provides an always-on, personalized service that customers can use to get help with their queries quickly and easily.
